,Not Recommended,287340,11744312,"Posted: 16 August, 2014",all,Bastwood,"Watered down tablet ""conversion"" of the original. I'm using quotation marks since, astonishingly, the game is actually not based on the original CMR, but Colin McRae Rally 2.0 instead. But it's not a conversion of CMR2 either, it's only using some of the cars and some of the assets of the original. The garage options have been stripped down, the number of cars have been cut and difficulty level generally made easier.For some bizarre reason the championship requires you to complete two consecutive six-leg rallies in one location before moving to the next, which I don't remember being a feature in the original. Didn't see any nighttime special stages either, and the damage model feels more forgiving.The end result is a game that kinda feels like the CMR games of yesteryear, but then again kinda doesn't and will just aggravate you more based on how well you remember the first few Colin games. They should've just straight up ported CMR1 and be done with it. This game, while serviceable, definitely will not satisfy the fans of the originals."
