,Not Recommended,287340,19492365,"Posted: 4 December, 2015",all,MysticNessly,"SHORT VERSION: This is a very lean game. Don't get me wrong. It's not a BAD game, but it isn't stellar.  There are much better racing games you can get at this price (or even lower)  (such as Sonic and All Stars Racing Transformed, Blur, Need for Speed Most Wanted 2012, Need for Speed Hot Pursuit 2010, Need for Speed the Run, and the Dirt series.LONGER VERSION:The entire game is pretty much time trials by yourself. Unfortunately you don't see your oponnents' cars. Each stage offers a different layout, but to advance to a different area, you have to play stages in the same area like 10 times. I got bored looking at the same environment and playing alone without AI cars.Controls feel just like the cars in the DiRT series, which is good. Your car becomes damaged if you bump into debris and trees. After like 2 races, you're given an option to make a limited number of repairs. With the limited ""repair time"" you must strategically choose which parts of the car you want to repair.Because of the slow progression through the game (it takes forever to see the different environments), and innability to see opponent cars or race alongside opponents, I cannot recommend this game at this price point.There are far better and fully fleshed-out games that can be purchased for about $5 which are much more fun."
