,Not Recommended,287340,24662681,"Posted: 1 August, 2016",all,DeltaDox,"Even on Steam sale I wanted my money back. If you are not familiar with this, this game is a mobile port of Colin McRae Rally to PC and it is not worth the money.For a PC port, the driving dynamics are flawed compared to the original CMR 2.0. You have horrendous understeer every time you want to attack a corner unless you use the handbrake but really it drops the car's momentum and you have to face the unbearable by watching your car slowly climb back up to top speed.The physics are also bad because the suspension model makes the car absorb the shock and pre load your car into the air sending it crashing.Though I know this is a port and I love Codemasters very much, they should have kept this title only exclusive for mobile phones."
