,Not Recommended,287340,29336729,Posted: 18 January,all,Archangel,"Some people won't be as harsh as me and, normally, I wouldn't post a negative review because there's always someone that thinks differently and starts the trolling ball rolling. But seriously, don't buy this game. It's not terrible - it's just not very good. Graphically, it can't handle 4k properly, even though the menu allows you to select it. (It's ok if you just want to see the top-right quarter of the screen - though maybe that's just my graphics card doing something odd). Don't leave it for ten minutes whilst you go away to make a sandwich, because when your wireless controller powers down, the game can't detect it again and you're forced to finish your rally using the keyboard. If all you have is your phone and a particularly dull journey, it might pass the time. If you've got an old laptop from 1995 that can't run anything else, ditto.There are many better driving games out there - many of them made by Codemasters, who are top of their game when it comes to this sort of thing. This is an easy pop at the handheld market and should never have gone anywhere near a PC. Get any of the other Colin McRae / DiRT games and you'll have a much better time of things.Trust me.I'm a doctor.(That's not true, I'm an accountant. But they're almost the same thing)."
